C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20Business%20Insider%20asked%20etiquette%20coach%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oldsouletiquette.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMariah%20Grumet%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20things%20passengers%20should%20avoid%20doing%20while%20on%20a%20flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20what%20she%20had%20to%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EReclining%20your%20seat%20without%20regard%20for%20others%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20gray%20tray%20in%20front%20of%20an%20aircraft%20seat.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b64ee2b4912df3ae1a6504%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EReclining%20your%20seat%20is%20OK%2C%20but%20be%20courteous%20to%20the%20person%20sitting%20behind%20you.%3Cp%3ECherdchanok%20Treevanchai%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20%E2%80%94%20or%20whether%20%E2%80%94%20to%20recline%20your%20seat%20on%20a%20flight%20is%20a%20hot%20topic%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-people-should-never-do-on-airplanes-flight-attendant-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplane%20etiquette%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrumet%20told%20BI%20that%20even%20though%20some%20may%20find%20it%20rude%2C%20she%20thinks%20passengers%20should%20be%20able%20to%20recline%20since%20they%20paid%20for%20their%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20she%20said%20passengers%20should%20still%20be%20mindful%20of%20the%20person%20sitting%20behind%20them%20when%20deciding%20when%20to%20recline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Grumet%20advises%20against%20reclining%20if%20the%20person%20behind%20you%20has%20things%20on%20their%20tray.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EStinking%20up%20the%20plane%20with%20food%20or%20grooming%20products%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224620%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20empty%20plate%20that%20food%20has%20been%20eaten%20off%20of%2C%20along%20with%20cutlery%20and%20dessert.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b65008b4912df3ae1a658d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223465%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAvoid%20bringing%20smelly%20food%20and%20toiletries%20on%20the%20plane.%3Cp%3EStephen%20Schauer%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGrumet%20said%20it's%20really%20important%20to%20be%20mindful%20of%20anything%20with%20a%20strong%20scent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20if%20a%20passenger%20brings%20a%20tuna%20sandwich%20onto%20the%20plane%2C%20the%20smell%20can%20be%20disturbing%20to%20those%20around%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrooming%20can%20come%20with%20extra%20smells%2C%20too.%20Items%20like%20nail%20polish%20or%20perfume%20could%20be%20distracting%20or%20irritating%20to%20fellow%20passengers%2C%20so%20Grumet%20advised%20leaving%20those%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBeing%20rude%20to%20parents%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20toddler's%20hand%20points%20against%20the%20window%20of%20an%20airplane.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b6531eb4912df3ae1a6757%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGiving%20parents%20dirty%20looks%20can%20just%20add%20fuel%20to%20the%20fire.%3Cp%3Ed3sign%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EYoung%20children%20may%20act%20out%20if%20they're%20hungry%20or%20exhausted%20from%20a%20long%20day.%20Even%20if%20the%20crying%20is%20annoying%20and%20disruptive%2C%20Grumet%20said%20it's%20important%20to%20be%20respectful%20to%20the%20parent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20likely%20that%20the%20parent%20is%20already%20super%20embarrassed%20as%20is%2C%20and%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20add%20fuel%20to%20the%20fire%20by%20whispering%20or%20giving%20dirty%20looks%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20also%20applies%20to%20children%20who%20are%20a%20bit%20ol