2%20alt%3D%5C%22Amazon%20CEO%20Andy%20Jassy%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6837ae2dc6ad288d148220dd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223641%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmazon%20CEO%20Andy%20Jassy%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FBrendan%20McDermid%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20initiative%20is%20notable%20for%20Amazon%2C%20which%20has%20spent%203%20decades%20relentlessly%20expanding%20its%20product%20catalog%20in%20pursuit%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-amazon-decided-to-sell-books-2018-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elimitless%3C%2Fa%3E%20online%20marketplace%20%E2%80%94%20a%20strategy%20that%20earned%20it%20the%20nickname%20%26quot%3BThe%20Everything%20Store.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20is%20still%20growing%20its%20vast%20selection%2C%20but%20the%20company%20is%20putting%20more%20focus%20on%20removing%20low-performing%20or%20inaccurate%20listings%20in%20favor%20of%20a%20more%20streamlined%20and%20effective%20catalog.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223dad8594-51c4-4702-875c-fc6ad0d07236%5C%22%3EStriking%20a%20tricky%20balance%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20almost%20infinite%20selection%20means%20shoppers%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20find%20what%20they're%20looking%20for%20on%20Amazon%2C%20increasing%20the%20chances%20they%20buy%20something%2C%20and%20return%20again.%20That's%20been%20a%20powerful%20advantage%20over%20physical%20retail%20stores%2C%20which%20can%20only%20stock%20so%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20is%20highly%20unlikely%20to%20give%20up%20the%20benefits%20of%20this%20massive%20product%20selection.%20However%2C%20some%20of%20the%20company's%20digital%20aisles%20have%20become%20cluttered%20and%20outdated%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20which%20could%20confuse%20or%20frustrate%20shoppers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStriking%20a%20balance%20between%20these%20two%20goals%20could%20be%20tricky%2C%20and%20Bend%20the%20Curve%20has%20been%20hotly%20debated%20internally%2C%20according%20to%20a%20person%20familiar%20with%20the%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Amazon%20shoppers%20may%20already%20be%20noticing.%20According%20to%20Evercore%20ISI's%20annual%20online%20retail%20survey%2C%20fewer%20respondents%20believe%20Amazon%20offers%20the%20best%20product%20selection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20a%20record-high%2084%25%20of%20respondents%20gave%20Amazon%20top%20marks%20for%20selection.%20That%20figure%20fell%20to%2079%25%20in%202023%2C%20and%20declined%20further%20to%2068%25%20last%20year%2C%20marking%20a%20record%20low%20in%20the%20survey's%2012-year%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2209df4f0c-0398-4186-9f58-4d70287d9976%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BPhasing%20out%20items%26quot%3B%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20email%20to%20BI%2C%20Amazon's%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20company%20will%20continue%20to%20expand%20its%20active%20product%20listings.%20The%20initiative%20is%20intended%20to%20clean%20up%20data%2C%20not%20curtail%20selection%2C%20the%20spokesperson%20said%2C%20adding%20Amazon%20added%20millions%20of%20new%20items%20to%20its%20product%20catalog%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20cost-reduction%20initiative%20in%20place%20to%20remove%20unhelpful%20data%2C%20including%20product%20listings%20that%20are%20inaccurate%2C%20incomplete%2C%20or%20in%20other%20ways%20fail%20to%20meet%20our%20listing%20requirements%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BThe%20aim%20is%20not%20to%20reduce%20active%20product%20listings.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20number%20of%20%26quot%3Bactive%20ASINs%26quot%3B%20does%20not%20correspond%20exactly%20with%20the%20actual%20product%20selection%20visible%20to%20customers%2C%20and%20reducing%20that%20number%20doesn't%20always%20equate%20to%20a%20reduction%20in%20selection.%20%26quot%3BUnproductive%20selection%26quot%3B%20includes%20items%20that%20can't%20be%20purchased%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20if%20there's%20no%20actual%20inventory%20to%20support%20a%20listing%2C%20or%20if%20product%20listings%20haven't%20been%20updated%20for%20more%20than%20two%20years%2C%20the%20spokesperson%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20teams%20regularly%20review%20product%20listings%20based%20on%20performance%2C%20quality%2C%20and%20evolving%20customer%20needs%20%E2%80%94%20and%20we've%20done%20this%20for%20many%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20added.%20%26quot%3BIn%20some%20cases%2C%20it%20may%20involve%20phasing%20out%20items%20that%20no%20longer%20meet%20our%20standards%20or%20are%20being%20replaced%20by%20newer%20versions.%20The%20goal%20is%20always%20to%20refine%2C%20not%20restrict%2C%20selection%2C%20ensuring%20our%20shopping%20experience%20meets%20the%20highest%20standards.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20spokesperson%20added%20that%20there%20was%20%26quot%3Bno%20debate%20in%20the%20sense%20of%20whether%20to%20proceed%26quot%3B%20with%20the%20Bend%20the%20Curve%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLeadership%20made%20clear%20throughout%20the%20process%20that%20the%20work%20should%20not%2C%20even%20by%20accident%2C%20negatively%20impact%20selling%20partners%20or%20remove%20selection%20from%20Amazon%2C%20and%20we%20put%20guardrails%20in%20place%20to%20ensure%20that%20didn't%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2204f31c2c-ebbb-4a1c-ae0f-c9612ed3bee2%5C%22%3E'Throttling'%20listings%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20Amazon%20has%20simplified%20the%20process%20of%20becoming%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-sellers-share-top-advice-for-making-money-through-ecommerce-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eseller%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20its%20platform.%20These%20third-party%20merchants%20are%20now%20responsible%20for%20more%20than%2060%25%20of%20all%20products%20sold%20on%20Amazon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20believes%20that%20growing%20the%20number%20of%20third-party%20sellers%20and%20expanding%20product%20selection%20fuel%20a%20flywheel%3A%20more%20choices%20lead%20to%20happier%20customers%2C%20attract%20more%20shoppers%2C%20and%20ultimately%20drive%20continued%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Amazon's%201999%20shareholder%20letter%2C%20founder%20Jeff%20Bezos%20envisioned%20a%20place%20where%20people%20could%20%26quot%3Bcome%20to%20find%20and%20discover%20anything%20and%20everything%20they%20might%20want%20to%20buy%20online.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22jeff%20bezos%201999%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5c8a7d436123ca38c322ec8b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221422%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJeff%20Bezos%20on%20The%20Tonight%20Show%20with%20Jay%20Leno.%3Cp%3EFred%20Prouser%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Amazon's%20drive%20to%20create%20a%20limitless%20aisle%20of%20products%20has%20come%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-avoid-buying-fake-item-amazon-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Echallenges%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20platform%20has%20faced%20issues%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-counterfeit-goods-inspection-ice-government-project-2020-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecounterfeit%3C%2Fa%3E%20goods%2C%20expired%20food%20items%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-agency-sues-amazon-420000-items-it-says-were-dangerous-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enon-compliant%3C%2Fa%3E%20products%2C%20leading%20to%20consumer%20complaints%20and%20regulatory%20scrutiny.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20has%20taken%20many%20steps%20to%20tackle%20counterfeit%20goods%20in%20the%20past.%20And%20with%20Bend%20the%20Curve%2C%20Amazon%20is%20putting%20other%20controlling%20measures%20in%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20Amazon%20launched%20a%20new%20%26quot%3Bcreation%20throttling%26quot%3B%20feature%20that%20blocks%20new%20product%20listings%20from%20some%20underperforming%20seller%20accounts%2C%20the%20internal%20document%20showed.%20The%20company%20targeted%20at%20least%2012%2C000%20active%20sellers%20with%20catalogs%20of%20more%20than%20100%2C000%20product%20listings%20and%20no%20sales%20in%20the%20previous%2012%20months%20as%20part%20of%20the%20program%2C%20according%20to%20the%20document.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20enforcement%20prevented%20more%20than%20110%20million%20new%20listings%20from%20being%20created%2C%20while%20nearly%203%2C000%20sellers%20got%20warning%20messages%20for%20being%20close%20to%20the%20throttling%20threshold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20document%20said%20some%20of%20the%20sellers%20exited%20enforcement%20by%20modifying%20their%20listings%20or%20increasing%20their%20sales.%20The%20initiative%20%26quot%3Bpromoted%20significant%20catalog%20cleanup%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBend%20the%20Curve%20also%20led%20to%20confusion%20among%20some%20sellers%20regarding%20the%20policy's%20scope.%20According%20to%20the%20document%2C%20only%20%26quot%3Bunproductive%26quot%3B%20accounts%20were%20affected.%20However%2C%20some%20sellers%20with%20multiple%20accounts%20mistakenly%20believed%20that%20their%20entire%20accounts%20were%20being%20blocked%20from%20creating%20new%20listings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20Amazon%20is%20focusing%20this%20year%20on%20more%20clearly%20%26quot%3Bdefining%20policy%20enforcement%20and%20communication%26quot%3B%20to%20avoid%20misunderstandings%2C%20the%20document%20said.%20The%20company%20is%20also%20analyzing%20deleted%20listings%20to%20determine%20if%20there%20are%20identifiable%20patterns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2299a8be85-a14a-453c-9cd7-1b4f57863950%5C%22%3E'Cost%20avoidance'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20removing%20or%20streamlining%20unproductive%20listings%2C%20Bend%20the%20Curve%20saved%20more%20than%20%2422%20million%20in%20AWS%20server%20costs%20in%202024%2C%20the%20document%20said.%20Amazon%20projected%20an%20additional%20%2436%20million%20in%20AWS%20server%20%26quot%3Bcost%20avoidance%26quot%3B%20in%202025%20as%20the%20initiative%20continues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon's%20retail%20division%20expected%20to%20spend%20approximately%20%245.7%20billion%20on%20AWS%20cloud%20infrastructure%20in%202025%2C%20a%2027%25%20increase%20from%20last%20year's%20%244.5%20billion%2C%20according%20to%20another%20internal%20planning%20document%20obtained%20by%20BI.%20That's%20a%20slower%20growth%20rate%20compared%20to%20the%20previous%20year%2C%20when%20AWS%20server%20costs%20rose%2036%25%20from%20about%20%243.3%20billion%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aekim%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eekim%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20Signal%2C%20Telegram%2C%20or%20WhatsApp%20at%20650-942-3061.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-securely-sharing-whistleblower-information-about-powerful-institutions-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ehere's%20our%20guide%20to%20sharing%20information%20securely%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-bend-curve-project-purges-billions-product-listings-everything-store-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1748595602000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682f334ac6ad288d1481a329%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-bend-curve-project-purges-billions-product-listings-everything-store-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20program%20aims%20to%20streamline%20the%20company's%20giant%20online%20marketplace%20by%20removing%20unproductive%20lis