ace%20appeared%20clean%20within%20months%2C%20ecological%20scars%20lingered%20deep%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20tropical%20waters%20like%20the%20Arabian%20Sea%2C%20warmer%20temperatures%20may%20speed%20up%20the%20natural%20breakdown%20of%20oil%20through%20microbial%20activity.%20But%20that%20only%20helps%20with%20lighter%20oil%20components.%20Heavier%20fuels%20like%20furnace%20oil%20%E2%80%94%20the%20kind%20leaked%20off%20Kochi%20%E2%80%94%20are%20sticky%2C%20slow%20to%20degrade%2C%20and%20more%20likely%20to%20sink%20and%20persist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECoastal%20ecosystems%20like%20mangroves%2C%20coral%20reefs%2C%20and%20mudflats%20are%20especially%20vulnerable.%20Oil%20can%20coat%20roots%20and%20smother%20oxygen%20exchange%2C%20leaving%20behind%20what%20ecologists%20call%20%E2%80%9Cecological%20dead%E2%80%9D%20zones%E2%80%9D%E2%80%94areas%20where%20life%20struggles%20to%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20cases%2C%20nature%20does%20bounce%20back%2C%20especially%20with%20targeted%20restoration%2C%20resilient%20species%2C%20and%20community%20monitoring.%20But%20in%20others%2C%20the%20damage%20changes%20the%20local%20ecology%20forever%2C%20altering%20which%20species%20survive%2C%20how%20food%20chains%20function%2C%20and%20how%20safe%20the%20area%20is%20for%20fishing%20and%20recreation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20while%20recovery%20is%20possible%2C%20the%20effects%20of%20an%20oil%20spill%20don%E2%80%99t%20simply%20vanish%20with%20time.%20They%20fade%20%E2%80%94%20slowly%2C%20unevenly%2C%20and%20sometimes%2C%20never%20completely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EMini%20Glossary%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Col%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3EFurnace%20Oil%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3EA%20heavy%2C%20thick%20fuel%20commonly%20used%20in%20ships%20and%20factories%2C%20it%20is%20slow%20to%20break%20down%20and%20difficult%20to%20clean%20when%20spilled%20in%20water.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Ce